🔐 Smart Door Automation System (IR + Servo + Logging)
🧠 1. System Overview

The system detects a person approaching the door using an IR proximity sensor, opens the door using a servo motor, and logs each event (entry/exit).

⚙️ 2. Components Required
Microcontroller (Arduino Uno / ESP32 / Raspberry Pi Pico)
IR Proximity Sensor
Servo Motor (SG90 or MG90S)
Buzzer (optional, for alert)
LED (status indicator)
Resistors + jumper wires
Power supply (5V)
(Optional) WiFi module / ESP32 for cloud logging
🔌 3. Circuit Connections (Arduino Example)

IR Sensor:

VCC → 5V
GND → GND
OUT → Digital Pin 2

Servo Motor:

VCC → 5V
GND → GND
Signal → Digital Pin 9

LED (optional):

Anode → Pin 13 (via resistor)
Cathode → GND
🔄 4. Working Logic (Core Flow)
IR sensor detects object (LOW or HIGH depending on module)
If object detected:
Open door (servo rotates to 90°)
Turn ON LED
Log: "Door Opened"
Wait for a few seconds
If no object:
Close door (servo returns to 0°)
Turn OFF LED
Log: "Door Closed"
